---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Thornveil"
  description="One engineer. Three SBIR wins. Six active defense programs. Thornveil builds defense AI at a pace that shouldn't be possible."
>
  <PageHero
    title="About Thornveil"
    subtitle="One engineer building defense technology that competes with teams of hundreds."
  />

  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="section-padding relative">
    <div class="container-max mx-auto">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-teal mb-6 reveal">Mission</p>
        <blockquote class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-light leading-relaxed text-white/80 reveal reveal-delay-1">
          "Thornveil builds defense technology at the edge — where constraints are tightest, timelines shortest, and the margin for error is zero. We move from concept to working prototype faster than teams ten times our size."
        </blockquote>
        <div class="mt-6 w-12 h-0.5 bg-teal reveal reveal-delay-2"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Founder -->
  <section class="section-padding relative bg-navy-dark/50">
    <div class="container-max mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-12 lg:gap-16">
        <!-- Bio -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-3">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-teal mb-6 reveal">Founder</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8 reveal reveal-delay-1">
            Jesse Heywood
          </h2>

          <div class="space-y-5 text-white/50 leading-relaxed reveal reveal-delay-2">
            <p>
              Marine. Arabic linguist trained at the Defense Language Institute. Software engineer.
              Machine learning researcher. The kind of person who wins SBIR awards and then builds
              the deliverable before the contract is signed.
            </p>
            <p>
              Thornveil exists to prove a thesis: one disciplined engineer with the right tools,
              deep domain expertise, and zero organizational overhead can outpace teams of dozens.
              Not in theory — in competitive federal acquisitions, with working code, passing tests,
              and shipping prototypes.
            </p>
            <p>
              The track record speaks for itself.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Track Record -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-2 reveal reveal-delay-3">
          <div class="bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/5 rounded-lg p-8 space-y-6">
            <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-teal mb-6">Track Record</h3>

            <div class="space-y-5">
              <div class="border-b border-white/5 pb-5">
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/80 mb-1">AI Digital Staff Officer</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-white/40 leading-relaxed">
                  Built for a Marine Corps training command. 8,400 lines Go, 4,400 lines TypeScript.
                  FIPS 140-3, CAC/PKI auth, 5 database backends, 12 AI tools, Microsoft 365 integration.
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="border-b border-white/5 pb-5">
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/80 mb-1">Thermal Drone Detection</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-white/40 leading-relaxed">
                  State-of-the-art deep learning model for thermal UAV detection.
                  80.4% mAP@50 at 1280px resolution on benchmark datasets.
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="border-b border-white/5 pb-5">
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/80 mb-1">Acoustic Swarm Comms</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-white/40 leading-relaxed">
                  GPS-denied positioning to 0.069m accuracy. Sub-centimeter ranging.
                  14 feasibility experiments, 177 tests passing.
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="border-b border-white/5 pb-5">
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/80 mb-1">Arabic NLP Research</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-white/40 leading-relaxed">
                  Grammatical error correction at 95.4% of SOTA with 1/10th model size.
                  Diacritization engine 62x smaller than state of the art. 2.29% DER.
                </div>
              </div>

              <div>
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/80 mb-1">S&T Decision Platform</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-white/40 leading-relaxed">
                  Technology radar, capital flow tracking, MCDA scoring — 44 NIST 800-53 controls.
                  Direct-to-Phase-II SBIR award for the U.S. Space Force.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Approach -->
  <section class="section-padding relative">
    <div class="container-max mx-auto">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-teal mb-6 reveal">The Approach</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-12 reveal reveal-delay-1">
        Speed through simplicity
      </h2>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <div class="text-6xl font-bold text-white/5 mb-4">01</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">No overhead</h3>
          <p class="text-white/40 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            No middle management. No six-month procurement cycles for a database decision.
            No meetings about meetings. Every hour goes to building.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="text-6xl font-bold text-white/5 mb-4">02</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">Prototype velocity</h3>
          <p class="text-white/40 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Concept to working code in days. Working code to SBIR win in weeks.
            Every proposal ships with a functioning prototype — not a slide deck.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-3">
          <div class="text-6xl font-bold text-white/5 mb-4">03</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">Full-stack depth</h3>
          <p class="text-white/40 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            From PyTorch model training on NVIDIA GH200s to Go backend servers to React tactical dashboards
            to LaTeX proposals. One person means one coherent vision, end to end.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section-padding relative bg-navy-dark">
    <div class="container-max mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight reveal">
        Let's build something.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-white/40 text-lg max-w-lg mx-auto reveal reveal-delay-1">
        If you have a hard problem and need it solved fast — not eventually — reach out.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-10 reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">
          Get in Touch
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5L21 12m0 0l-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
